Fires shot out of Thassalin's throat, as the massive Thracian set a certain woodland area in bounds and then circled over it to detect movement. Notably, the eerie screeching behind him subsided as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
“What's the matter, Tenuk, you've turned into a Thracian before!”
“When I fly myself, it's quite different from being suddenly yanked up by a gigantic pink dragon!”
“It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?”
Kayel was clearly not Nyssis' opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deep into Thassalin's back that the Thracian was bleeding. Thassalin seemed not to mind, however. Nonetheless, he realized he had frightened his new friends, and landed on a clearing.
“I APOLOGIZE, BUT I SMELLED SOMETHING. I HAD TO WORRY ABOUT IT THEN!”
“But did you have to drag us along too?” growled Tenuk as he climbed off Thassalin's back and slid down onto his tail. “And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our big, strong warrior! How is he going to catch up with us?”
“He'll come up with something…”, growled Nyssi. “Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not dumb.”
“True, but can Retvik drive?”
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. “Of course he can drive.”
“Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I haven't seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's. Also, he only started using the car for work because you always drive us. He only had his bike.”
Peals of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something extremely funny, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took a bit to calm him down.
“I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR HUGE FRIEND ON A LITTLE BIKE FOR TEMTHAN KIDS. IT WAS KILLING ME! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. IT WAS A WONDERFUL IMAGINATION! ONE I CANNOT SHARE!”
Kayel chuckled, thinking he could guess what was going on in Thassalin's head. “Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly fly off?”
Thassalin grunted, took off, and disappeared. When he returned after a short time, he threw something lifeless in front of Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, gold-white dragon creature. But it was missing its head. “ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR YOUR SCREAMS. I SMELL YOUR BLOOD. SOMETHING IS DRIVING ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. JUST LIKE YISINI ORDERS. THEY ARE VERY CLOSE.”
The mighty Thracian froze suddenly.  Nyssi and Kayel also froze and looked attentively at a gap in the clearing.  Something big and black stared at them and hissed.  What it was, it spread out two enormous wing pairs and shot at Thassalin without caring about the three smaller creatures between them.  Kayel and Tenuk could just barely take cover, but Nyssi was swept up and almost tossed onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by grabbing Nyssi and tossing him with his incredibly long, skilled tail onto his back, before he himself sprang into the air.  The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel snorted in annoyance, while he took down his gun from his back and opened a bag containing a cartridge belt.  He hung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thracian, and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?"
"You want to pursue them?"
„Ja, natürlich!“
„Aber… One of them is a huge monster!“
„Yes and? I'm standing here with a high-caliber gun in my hand and could shoot at it right away. But, well, how should I say – I would have to see it first, so that I can hit it.“
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to have more space. With a soft, pained grunting sound, Tenuk's body stretched out in length, his fur turned to scales and his arms turned to wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, light blue Thracian, but his eyes remained red.
„Get on.“
Like a normal-looking Thracian, Tenuk now had a proper scaly shield running along his back. Conveniently, a pair of spines had also grown on his back, allowing Kayel to hold on to him. It took a bit of time for Tenuk to get airborne, but once he was in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel soon realized that they weren't alone. A second dark creature shot up under them, and Tenuk could only barely avoid a collision.
"Is that the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to shoot at the second creature, missed it, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk didn't respond. He was too busy concentrating on flying in the direction of Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature following them. Kayel turned around awkwardly to keep the monster in his sights. The fact that it was following them was a benefit for Kayel, as he could easily aim and fire. Two shots went through the upper wings of the creature. It let out a pain-filled roar and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it wouldn't be able to keep up with them anytime soon.
A good distance ahead of them, Nyssi clung desperately to Thassalin's back as the massive creature swung its arms and spat flames at the charred monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed furious but not ready to give up. The fireballs seemed to have no effect. When Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw his own weapon, a good old shotgun. It wasn't the first choice, but maybe the shot would scare off the black creature.
